# What You Learned Today

## `StatefulWidget`

We switched from `StatelessWidget` because the password visibility changes while the app is running.

---

## `hidePassword`

```dart
bool hidePassword = true;
```

This variable keeps track of whether the password is hidden.

---

## `setState()`

```dart
setState(() {
  hidePassword = !hidePassword;
});
```

Whenever the value changes, Flutter redraws the screen.

You'll use `setState()` frequently in Flutter.

---

## `Navigator.push()`

```dart
Navigator.push(...)
```

Unlike `pushReplacement()`, this allows users to return to the previous screen by pressing the back button.

